rComments: Prof.Panthaki was and is the best thing that happened to UTSC and UofT in general. Too bad because of the stupid President losing everyone's money they had to lay him off. It would help if UofT wasn't so nepotist and actually hired profs that were good, taught well and knew their stuff. Rather than just people who like to PROFESS their knowledge!

Took the course a few years back as a distance studies.  I was worried at how this would turn out, but he is so clear that you need not worry about having to ask any questions.  He was on loan from the military.

He is the best, and like everyone else said these were video lectures!  It was better than most classes where the prof is actually in front of you in class and make you go to sleep! How come he was only subbing?
He' describes everything in detail and has a very good lecture setup. And he's also quite good looking. =)
excellent Prof/ The best Prof I ever had
He is a very nice and helpfull man. I really like him a lot. (Hassan Y.)
Great Professor! So interesting, and makes you love History! He knows a lot about genealogy too! Over all, one of the best Profs you will ever see!!

He's an excellent professor. After taking his class, I've decided to major in history. I've never seen an individual so passionate about his work. I hope he teaches more courses. It was definitely worth going to all his lectures. The man knows his material. Plus, he's appealing to the eyes! :)
